		<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
		<br />
		<h4>What can I wager my credits on?</h4>
		<p>There are leagues for the NFL, College Bowl Season, March Madness, &amp; World Cup Soccer. 
		There are a variety of bet types, including the spread, the moneyline, over/under, and props.</p>
		<br />
		<h4>Do I have to risk something on every game?</h4>
		<p>No. Only wager on what you want. You could try every single game for a week or none at all. Totally up to you. Unlike fantasy football, there
		is no effective punishment for taking a week off.</p>
		<br />
		<h4>What is the moneyline and how does it work?</h4>
		<p>You can learn more about the moneyline, parlays, over/under and the rest in our handy <a href="/front/betting_guide">betting guide</a>.</p>
		<br />
		<h4>Can I parlay games?</h4>
		<p>Yes, we love parlays because they are awesome. To encourage them, Sharp League calculates payouts according to their 
		<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parlay_(gambling)##Odds_and_payout" target="_blank">true odds</a>.
		</p>
		<br />
		<h4>Is this legal?</h4>
		<p>Yes. Although Sharp League mimics the action of a sportsbook, it does not take in or pay out any real money. We consider it a fantasy game. 
		If the commissioner of a tournament wants to run a side pool, it is his or her responsibility to do so fairly and legally.</p>
